<br>
But heck lets face it the only exploits anyone should realy be worrying about and having a fit over are the ones that are grounds for disiplinary action.  Heck the only exploits VERANT worrys about and labbles exploits are the ones that have grounds for diciplinary action.  Take the horse bugg were people were getting the standing mana regen without graffics.  Verant never came out and said it was an exploit, becase the moment they had done that then everyone doing it would be breaking a rule and subject to disiplinary warning is caught.  And sence so many people did it they just fixed the problem instead.<br>
<br>
So on that note, it's not an &quot;Official&quot; exploit worth worrying about tell verant says it is or does something about it.  And if it's not an official exploit it is not an exploit in the terms of the definition of what is and isn't an exploit that people seem to be trying to apply there definitions too.<br>
<br>
Everything that dosn't fall in my definition of an exploit I will call non esential exploits for all those that want to make a definition up for NON esential exploits.<br>
<br>
Unless of course your on some crusade to get a verant employee to read about a bugg and finaly do something about it to fix it, or even make it officialy grounds for disciplinary action if people keep doing it.  Like happened with horses.<br>
