<br>
Coren you are either not a wizard, or are a low level one that hasn't used these types of spells, or are a complete idiot of a wizard, at any rate your obviously Confused.  Wizards have 3 seperate kinds of AE spells, let me elighten you.<br>
<br>
Rain spells - These target one mob but hit the said mob 3 times.  Rains can hit ONE mob THREE times OR they can hit 3 mobs once, OR they can hit two mobs were one is hit twice and one is hit once.  Reguardless, rains have 3 waves that happen in succession of eachuther unless more then on mob is in range of it.  These are normaly used for single targets becase they can deal out some nice damage IF the waves arn't resisted.<br>
<br>
Pillar colum spells - these spells are cast on a target and hit up to 4 targets and are specificaly desined to hit up to 4 targets if 4 targets are in range.  These are normaly used for quadding.<br>
<br>
Person Based AE's - these spell can hit an unlimited number of targets as long as they are in range and are centered on the caster.  These are normaly used for AE groups and farming green mobs.<br>
