<br>
I was under the impression (and I believe I've actually done the 2-mob scenario before) that rains had 3 waves, but a maximum of 4 hits total (excluding pets).  <br>
<br>
i.e.  <br>
One-mob scenario: you can hit one mob 3 times, <br>
Two-mob scenario: two mobs get hit 2 times each (and the 3rd wave won't do anything) <br>
Three-mob scenario: all 3 get hit on the first wave, 1 gets hit on the 2nd wave, and nothing gets hit on the 3rd wave.<br>
<br>
It's a real pain in the ass to get 2 mobs close enough together to hit em with the same rain, plus keep aggro off yourself so they stand there long enough to get hit by both waves, so I haven't done it often.  You've got me curious now, though, so I'll have to go try this.<br>
