LIC START--><em>exploit</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> this is not the case.<br>
<br>
An exploit, as stated, is a noble or heroic act, so I won't choose to describe bugs that are exploited as this. I'd like to encourage proper use of grammar and vocabulary. <br>
<br>
An exploit of a bug is exactly what is already stated; someone making use of a bug for their own benefit, or to better understand what the bug is. More often it is their making use of it for their own benefit.<br>
<br>
